# UI and Glassmorphism Rules

## Positive Directives

- Default to dark mode (deep black background: #0a0a0a)
- Use the `glass` CSS class for all card-like containers (provides backdrop-blur and translucent borders)
- Use the `glass-hover` class for interactive glass elements
- Use the `GlassCard` and `GlassButton` components from `@/components/ui/` as building blocks
- Typography must be bold, high-contrast, and use tight tracking (`tracking-tighter` for headlines)
- Headlines should be UPPERCASE for the Nike-inspired aesthetic
- Use `text-muted` (zinc-400) for secondary text, `text-foreground` (white) for primary
- Use `rounded-2xl` for card border radius consistently
- Use subtle transitions (`transition-all duration-300 ease`) on all interactive elements

## Negative Rules

- NEVER use cluttered layouts with excessive borders, shadows, or gradients
- NEVER use a light/white background as the default theme
- NEVER use standard HTML buttons without the GlassButton component styling
- NEVER mix serif and sans-serif fonts
- NEVER use colors outside the defined theme palette without explicit approval

## Verification Steps

- Visually confirm all cards use the frosted-glass effect (backdrop-blur)
- Check that interactive elements have smooth hover transitions
- Verify dark mode renders correctly with high contrast between text and background
